{{REPRODUCTION_STEPS}}

## Root-cause hypothesis (your understanding — agent will verify)
{{ROOT_CAUSE_HYPOTHESIS}}

## Hard constraints
- {{CONSTRAINTS}}

## Output instructions — follow this exact sequence

### Step 1 — Root cause analysis
Exact line(s) responsible. What assumption is violated? Single-site or pattern?

### Step 2 — Regression test (RED)
Test that reproduces the bug and fails on current code.
Full class with package declaration and imports.
Conform to checkstyle if config provided ({{CHECKSTYLE_PATH}}).

### Step 3 — Additional edge-case tests (RED)
Up to 3 closely related edge cases. State "No additional edge cases" if none.

### Step 4 — Fix (GREEN)
Minimal fix. Full fixed class. Annotate each changed line with inline comment.
Checkstyle conformance required.

### Step 5 — Verify existing tests still pass
Explicit inspection confirmation. Flag any test passing for the wrong reason.

### Step 6 — Build and run command
  {{BUILD_TOOL_PATH}} ... (with {{JVM_ARGS}} injected appropriately)

### Step 7 — Diff summary
Per changed line: file, what changed, why.

### Step 8 — Review notes
- Isolated or symptomatic of wider pattern?
- Follow-up recommendations.
